Gwamnan Kansas City ya yi farin ciki da taimakon ƙasa a magance hare-haren, amma ya yi tsoron manufofin Trump.
Shugaban Kansas City, Quinton Lucas, ya tambaye a ranar Lahadi game da nufin da Shugaban Amurka, Trump, ya yi na aika wa 'yan sanda na Amurka zuwa birane a cikin Amurka - yana cewa, yayin da zai amince da taimakon wajen magance yawan kisan da ake yi a birnin tsakiya na Midwestern, ya gaskata cewa wannan mataki zai iya zama game da tabbatar da nasara a zaben sake shigarwa da Trump.
"Na yi mamaki sosai wannan mako [da] shugaban ya ambaci bikin nuna goyon bayan George Floyd, ya ambaci kungiyar Black Lives Matter," Lucas, wanda yake cikin jam'iyyar Dimokuradiyya, ya ce a shirin "Fox News Sunday" game da bikin nuna goyon bayan da aka yi akan rashin adalci tsakanin al'umma da kuma zalunci da sojoji.
Ba haka yake a Kansas City ba. Mun samu karuwar shekara-a-shekara [amma] abin da muke buƙata taimako a kan shi shi ne gaggawa wasu daga cikin mazauna bata da gaskiya.
Lucas ya ƙara da cewa: "Muna ƙoƙarin ƙirƙirar hankali mai ƙarfi da ƙarfi akan magance kisan kai ... Ina ganin idan ku saurari bayanai na ƙarshe ... muna farin ciki da aiki tare da 'yan sanda na ƙasa a cikin ƙaramin yanayi."
Bayan ƙaunarsa da ake yi wa masu aikin ƙungiyar ƙasa da yin aiki tare da hukumomin yankin, Lucas ya ce maganganun Trump - musamman a cikin alamun tashin hankali da aka samu akan hanyoyin da aka yi amfani da su a Portland, Ore., daga masu aikin ƙungiyar ƙasa - ya sa mutane da yawa daga cikin masu zaɓen sa suka yi magana game da halin da masu aikin suke cikin birane.
