ISLAMABAD (AP) - Shugaban ƙarƙashin ƙasa na Majalisar Dinkin Duniya da aka zaba a ranar Lahadi ya sanar da cewa ya yanke shawarar jinkirta ziyarar da ya shirya yi wa Pakistan saboda wasu matsaloli na jirgin sama.
Diplomasiyar Turkiyya Volkan Bozkir ya zama shugaban ƙarƙashin 75 na Majalisar Dinkin Duniya a watan da ya gabata, kuma an tsara shi ya iso Islamabad ranar Lahadi.
Amma a cikin rubutun Twitter, ya ce ziyarar babban birnin Pakistan za ta yi jinkiri.
Ministan kasashen waje na Pakistan, Shah Mahmood Qureshi, ya aika tweet a matsayin amsar Bozkir cewa "Ina fatan zaku zo Pakistan nan da nan don ziyara mai amfani da ci gaba da amfani."
Ranar da ta gabata, Qureshi mai farin ciki, yayin sanar da ziyarar, ya yi fatan zai tattauna batutuwa da dama tare da Bozkir, ciki har da Kashmir, wanda aka raba tsakanin Pakistan da ƙasar da take ɓangaren gabashin India, kuma ake ƙudurin ƙarƙashinsa a matsayin gaba ɗaya.
Pakista da Indiya sun yi biyu daga cikin uku daga yankunan da suka yi kisan kai tun da suka samu ƙarfin ƙasar ta daga mulkin Turawan Biritaniya a shekarar 1947.
A yau da kullum, biyu ƙasashe suna yin kai-tsaye a Kashmir, wanda ya haifar da raunuka ga jami'an tsaro da jama'a a dukkan biyu ƙasashe.
Pakistan ta nema Gwamnatin Tarayya ta yi amfani da dokoki dake cikin sauyin da ta yi game da batun Kashmir, ta bai wa mutane da suke zaune a yankin Himalaya damar zabar yadda za su hada kai da India ko Pakistan, ko kuma su zabi ƙarƙashin ƙarfi.
